[1] Cholera - Congo DR (South Kivu Province)
Date: Fri 17 Jan 2014
Source: Radio Okapi [in French, mach. trans., edited]
http://radiookapi.net/regions/sud-kivu/2014/01/17/sud-kivu-le-cholera-fait-3-morts-en-3-semaines-sange/


In the space of 3 weeks, 224 cholera cases and 3 deaths have been recorded in the general hospital in Ruzizi in Sange [South Kivu Province], the chief physician of area of health has indicated Friday [17 Jan 2014]. For the physician director of the general hospital of Ruzizi in Sange, Ndugu Kanyegere, the resurgence of this disease is related to the non-compliance of the rules of hygiene by the population. He has also called on the community to "well observe the measures of food hygiene, especially the water that they drink."

