[5] Cholera - Myanmar (Kachin State)
Date: Wed 22 Jan 2014
Source: Mizzima [edited]
http://www.mizzima.com/mizzima-news/myanmar/item/10838-cholera-outbreak-reported-in-kachin-refugee-camp


Emergency supplies of medicine are needed for an outbreak of cholera in a camp housing civilians displaced by conflict in Kachin State's Mansi Township, a health care worker has told Mizzima.

The medical in-charge of the Mine Khaung refugee camp, La Htaw Naw Lai, said on 20 Jan 2014 that more than 50 children had been diagnosed with cholera at the start of the month, but the number with the disease had since declined.

Medicine was also needed to treat an outbreak of colds in the camp, La Htaw Naw Lai said. "We are having problems because we are running out of medicine in the camp," he said. He said a charity organization in the state capital, Myitkyina, had helped to ease a food shortage in the camp by supplying bags of rice, but the refugees needed more nutrition in their diet. La Htaw Naw Lai said there was also a shortage of drinking water and adequate shelter.

The camp houses more than 700 people from 3 villages, who were forced to flee their homes late in 2013 because of fighting between government forces and the Kachin Independence Army.

